  "body": "### Component\n\nForge\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [X] Foundry\n- [ ] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\nforge 0.2.0 (34f684d 2023-11-01T22:19:24.989266000Z)\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\nforge test\n\n### Operating System\n\nNone\n\n### Describe the bug\n\nThe following code reverts.\r\n(on a very strange error, `[FAIL. Reason: EvmError: Revert] setUp() (gas: 0)`, even though there is no \"setUp()\")\r\n\r\nChanging the \"constructor\" to \"setUp\" works.\r\n\r\n```solidity\r\ncontract TestBalance is Test {\r\n\r\n    address addr = address(0x1234);\r\n\r\n    function initBalance() internal {\r\n        payable(addr).transfer(1 ether);\r\n    }\r\n//    function setUp() public {\r\n    constructor() {\r\n        initBalance();\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n",
